notes.note:
I replied:
RE: Warranty contract number W-186293

Thank you for your email.
The purpose of the warranty is to cover repair to components listed as covered under in the warranty.
All parts listed in Covered Components are covered. Any parts not listed are also not covered.
The clutch for your vehicle is not listed and therefore not covered. Replacement and/or machining of the flywheel due to the clutch failure is also not covered since it is consequential damage caused by the clutch failure.
This is not a matter of assessing blame as to who or what caused this failure. It is simply that the clutch is not covered and consequential damage from the failure of a non-covered component is also not covered.
Unfortunately, we must decline any coverage or offer of settlement since the failure is clearly not within the coverage of the warranty.

Respectfully,
Adam Halko
